# Styles Organization

The [src/styles/](mdc:src/styles) directory contains all CSS for the desktop simulation and app modules.

## Main Files
- [main.css](mdc:src/styles/main.css): Main stylesheet, imports shared and GUI-specific CSS.

## Subdirectories
- [gui/](mdc:src/styles/gui): Styles for desktop, windows, taskbar, start menu, icons, and iframes.
  - [window.css](mdc:src/styles/gui/window.css): Window styling.
  - [taskbar.css](mdc:src/styles/gui/taskbar.css): Taskbar styling.
  - [startMenu.css](mdc:src/styles/gui/startMenu.css): Start menu styling.
  - [desktop.css](mdc:src/styles/gui/desktop.css): Desktop styling.
  - [icons.css](mdc:src/styles/gui/icons.css): Icon styling.
  - [iframeApp.css](mdc:src/styles/gui/iframeApp.css): Iframe app styling.
- [utils/](mdc:src/styles/utils): Utility and effect styles.
  - [reset.css](mdc:src/styles/utils/reset.css): CSS reset for consistency.
  - [boot.css](mdc:src/styles/utils/boot.css): Boot sequence styling.
  - [login.css](mdc:src/styles/utils/login.css): Login screen styling.
  - [crt.css](mdc:src/styles/utils/crt.css): CRT effect styling.

## Conventions
- App modules may include their own `style.css` but should import shared styles for consistency.
- Follow pixel-perfect and UI conventions in [docs/ISSUES.md](mdc:docs/ISSUES.md).

